I’m a bunch of voices in Diablo 4.

All over the place as various barbarians and bosses.. you’ll likely kill me a lot .. and hear me talk about pain and misery and such.

Diablo 1 was one of the first games I became absorbed with.. in a magical word outside of my own and helped spark my imagination/curiosity that developed me into who I am today. 

20 some odd years later here I am helping create another new world in that same franchise. I am so thankful to @toyingwithu @thejbblanc and @blizzard for letting me participate in the story.

#diablo #blizzard

I’m a Voice in Elder Scrolls! This one is special in particular because I am a Bard named Vevos Sarano! I was given the opportunity to sing several different songs throughout! Taking me back to my Musical touring days

Andrew Gamer nerd fact:
Back in the early 2000s I was playing oblivion and found out if I made my character sneak into a wall behind a merchant, that would level up my sneak ability.

So for hours I used a rubber band on my controller, and put wrapped the other end around a weight… and when I came back I was maxed out.

One of many adventures I’ve had in the world of Elder scrolls, and that kid still in my heart spending countless hours in morrowind, oblivion, and Skyrim is floored about this.

Thanks for the incredible opportunity @tamriel_adventurers and for the fantastic guidance/direction by none other then @redheadsaidprod
